df\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_6812836\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_6812836\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">März 20, 2026</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104myt1714308484693.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/myt1714308484693.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/myt1714308484693.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"myt1714308484693\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Uniface enables you to determine if the data in a string value matches a desired pattern\n\t\tusing regex strings. A regex string is a regular expression enclosed in forward slashes\n\t\t\t(‘<code class=\"ph codeph\">/</code>’).</p>\n<p class=\"p\">Regex strings can be used to specify a field syntax, such as postal code or telephone\n\t\t\tnumber. They are also useful when searching for and comparing or replacing strings. For\n\t\t\texample, they can be used when:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"myt1714308484693__ul_n41_krp_fbc\">\n<li class=\"li\">Defining logical expressions with the <code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">==</code>, and\n\t\t\t\t\t<code class=\"ph codeph\">!=</code> operators in conditional ProcScript statements\n\t\t\t\t\t(<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">if</span>, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">repeat</span>,\n\t\t\t\t<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">selectcase</span>, or <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">while</span>). </li>\n<li class=\"li\">Searching and replacing strings using <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">scan</span>,\n\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$scan</span>, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$rscan</span>,\n\t\t\t\t<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$replace</span>. </li>\n<li class=\"li\">Truncating strings using <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$ltrim</span> and\n\t\t\t\t<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$rtrim</span>.</li>\n<li class=\"li\">Splitting a string using <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$split</span>.</li>\n<li class=\"li\">Explicitly converting data to a specified data type using\n\t\t\t\t<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$typed</span>.</li>\n</ul>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"myt1714308484693__section_n51_j1q_fbc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d395418e119\">Example: Using Regex Strings</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">To represent the pattern of a Canadian postal code (such as B2Y 5K2), the regex\n\t\t\t\tstring would be <code class=\"ph codeph\">/[A-Z]\\d[A-Z] \\d[A-Z]\\d/</code>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">To enforce this pattern in a data entry field, you can specify this regex string in\n\t\t\t\tthe <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Field Syntax</span> property.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">In ProcScript, you can use <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$regex</span> to convert a string to a regex\n\t\t\t\tstring, and use this to search for a matching string. For example:</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104myt1714308484693_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"myt1714308484693__codeblock_gwg_bbq_fbc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">;Field ADDRESS = \"Mary John, 2 Ginger Lane, Genoa NS B0R 1N6\"\n; Scan the string for a substring that matches the postal code pattern, \n; and return the position of the matching string\nvLocation = $scan (ADDRESS, $regex(\"[A-Z]\\d[A-Z] \\d[A-Z]\\d\"))\n; If a position is returned, issue a message\nif (vLocation &gt; 0)\n  putmess \"A postal code is provided\"\nendif</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"myt1714308484693__section_jf2_dbq_fbc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d395418e146\">Syntax of Regex Strings</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">Regex strings (regular expressions) provide a powerful way to specify patterns for\n\t\t\t\ttext matching and manipulation. The syntax of regex strings used in Uniface conforms\n\t\t\t\tto a Modified ECMAScript regular expression grammar, which is a widely accepted\n\t\t\t\tstandard for defining regex patterns.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">Regex strings (regular expressions) are a versatile tool for defining complex\n\t\t\t\tpatterns in text. While they are powerful, they can also be complex. For detailed\n\t\t\t\tguidance on constructing regex patterns and utilizing advanced features, refer to\n\t\t\t\tthe ECMAScript regular expression syntax documentation.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"myt1714308484693__section_qjz_jq1_4cc\">\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table frame-all\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"myt1714308484693__table_evy_ypg_q3c\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Related learning videos</span></caption><colgroup><col style=\"width:50%\"/><col style=\"width:50%\"/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\">\n<th class=\"entry colsep-1 rowsep-1\" id=\"myt1714308484693__table_evy_ypg_q3c__entry__1\">Title</th>\n<th class=\"entry colsep-1 rowsep-1\" id=\"myt1714308484693__table_evy_ypg_q3c__entry__2\">link</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\">\n<td class=\"entry colsep-1 rowsep-1\" headers=\"myt1714308484693__table_evy_ypg_q3c__entry__1\">Regular Expressions</td>\n<td class=\"entry colsep-1 rowsep-1\" headers=\"myt1714308484693__table_evy_ypg_q3c__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\"><a class=\"xref\" href=\"https://vimeo.com/showcase/10552636/video/953958584\" rel=\"external noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"Click to watch or listen Regular Expressions video\" class=\"image\" id=\"myt1714308484693__image_fps_d3w_q3c\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/My_Video_Button.jpg?_LANG=enus\"/></a></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_6812836\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_6812836\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Regex Strings for Pattern Matching Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated März 20, 2026 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Uniface enables you to determine if the data in a string value matches a desired pattern using regex strings. A regex string is a regular expression enclosed in forward slashes (‘ / ’). Regex strings can be used to specify a field syntax, such as postal code or telephone number. They are also useful when searching for and comparing or replacing strings. For example, they can be used when: Defining logical expressions with the = , == , and != operators in conditional ProcScript statements ( if , repeat , selectcase , or while ). Searching and replacing strings using scan , $scan , $rscan , $replace . Truncating strings using $ltrim and $rtrim . Splitting a string using $split . Explicitly converting data to a specified data type using $typed . Example: Using Regex Strings To represent the pattern of a Canadian postal code (such as B2Y 5K2), the regex string would be /[A-Z]\\d[A-Z] \\d[A-Z]\\d/ . To enforce this pattern in a data entry field, you can specify this regex string in the Field Syntax property. In ProcScript, you can use $regex to convert a string to a regex string, and use this to search for a matching string. For example: Explain this code ;Field ADDRESS = \"Mary John, 2 Ginger Lane, Genoa NS B0R 1N6\" ; Scan the string for a substring that matches the postal code pattern, ; and return the position of the matching string vLocation = $scan (ADDRESS, $regex(\"[A-Z]\\d[A-Z] \\d[A-Z]\\d\")) ; If a position is returned, issue a message if (vLocation > 0) putmess \"A postal code is provided\" endif Copy Syntax of Regex Strings Regex strings (regular expressions) provide a powerful way to specify patterns for text matching and manipulation. The syntax of regex strings used in Uniface conforms to a Modified ECMAScript regular expression grammar, which is a widely accepted standard for defining regex patterns. Regex strings (regular expressions) are a versatile tool for defining complex patterns in text. While they are powerful, they can also be complex. For detailed guidance on constructing regex patterns and utilizing advanced features, refer to the ECMAScript regular expression syntax documentation. Table 1. Related learning videos Title link Regular Expressions Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}